&lt;p&gt;The Brattle Group: Associate (Multiple Positions) - Boston, MA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUTIES:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and manage projects in team environment to produce written analyses used in litigation, regulatory proceedings, international arbitration, and consulting engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop statistical, econometric, and other quantitative data analysis and oversee analysis performed by Research Analysts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft reports that summarize and explain the results of analytical work performed, using clear and concise writing that presents technical concepts in a manner accessible to noneconomists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for project management, including keeping the client informed of new developments and responding to client requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for overseeing the final work product for the following: reports, client memos, proposals, presentations, data requests, interrogatories, and expert witness testimony in a litigation and non-litigation environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist counsel with preparing expert witness for deposition and trial testimony, cross-examination and deposition of opposing expert witnesses, and drafting of post-trial briefs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for participating in business development activities including drafting business development materials, drafting proposals and budgets, speaking at conferences, and publishing in professional and trade journals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;REQUIREMENTS: Ph.D. or foreign equivalent in Economics, Finance or related quantitative field&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Master’s degree or foreign equivalent in Economics, Finance or related quantitative field + 3 years of experience consulting on financial and/or economic concepts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualified candidate must possess any amount of experience with or demonstrated knowledge* of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quantitative analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical/statistical software include STATA, R, SQL and Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex financial and economic related concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Knowledge may be demonstrated through education, training and / or experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TELEWORK: Position may be authorized to work at any Brattle Group office within the US or for full or part time telework&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TRAVEL: Up to 10% domestic travel required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SALARY: $193,900 to $220,448 per year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LOCATION: One Beacon Street, Suite 2600, Boston, MA, 02108&lt;/p&gt;
