&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Brattle Australia&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Brattle Group, a privately held, global economic consulting firm, is seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Associate&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing securities practice in Sydney. For over a decade, Brattle’s Sydney office has been at the forefront of delivering market-leading corporate finance and economic consulting capabilities across Australia. As we continue to grow, we are looking for talented individuals to join our high-performing team. Our Australia-based professionals work side by side with clients to tackle their most complex challenges, developing novel and rigorous approaches that make a real impact. From assessing economic and commercial damages to shaping innovative solutions and bringing global insights to local markets, we are committed to delivering exceptional analysis and client service—and to building a team where you can do your best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Our Work&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Securities group at Brattle in Sydney works on complex, high-stakes disputes involving shareholder claims, regulatory investigations, and expert evidence. Our work includes analysing alleged corporate misconduct and disclosures, assessing materiality and investor impact, building trading and damages models, and critically evaluating opposing expert analyses. The team combines financial economics, accounting, and data analysis to quantify losses and support litigation strategy in fast-moving, high-profile cases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;The Role&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Associates work as part of a team on challenging and high-profile projects in a collegial and fast-paced work environment. Brattle is sought after to answer complex financial, economic, and regulatory questions for clients around the world. You will have an opportunity to support our Principals, Academic Advisors, and Outside Experts as they serve as expert witnesses before courts and arbitration panels on behalf of law firms, corporations, and government agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide our Associates with a variety of experiences and individualised development with increasing responsibilities. Associates are central members of each project team, and they apply finance, accounting, and economic concepts to help resolve high-profile engagements, including litigation, corporate strategy regulation, and public policy on behalf of our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
