&lt;p&gt;The Brattle Group, a privately held, global economic consulting firm, is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Director of Global Workplace Operations &lt;/strong&gt;to join our&lt;strong&gt; Washington, DC &lt;/strong&gt;office. The Director of Global Workplace Operations is responsible for ensuring highly skilled and high-performing administrative support teams, efficient and effective facilities services and the effective execution and management of the firm’s real estate operations in support of firm leadership and business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role provides global leadership across workplace operations, administrative services, facilities and space management, and real estate portfolio management in support of firmwide operational and workplace strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position reports to the VP of Operations, is part of the Corporate Services management team, and works closely with local Office Directors and firm leadership to ensure that operational services and physical infrastructure are aligned with the firm’s business objectives, growth plans, and evolving workplace needs.&lt;/p&gt;
