&lt;p&gt;The Brattle Group, a privately held, global economic consulting firm, is seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Research Associate&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing competition practice in Sydney. For over a decade, Brattle’s Sydney office has been at the forefront of delivering market-leading corporate finance and economic consulting capabilities across Australia. As we continue to grow, we are looking for talented individuals to join our high-performing team. Our Australia-based professionals work side by side with clients to tackle their most complex challenges, developing novel and rigorous approaches that make a real impact. From assessing economic and commercial damages to shaping innovative solutions and bringing global insights to local markets, we are committed to delivering exceptional analysis and client service—and to building a team where you can do your best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Our Work&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The competition practice at Brattle in Sydney includes classic competition matters such as mergers and misuses of market power, in addition to other matters requiring a detailed understanding of competition and/or empirical analysis, including estimating damages and market studies. Much of our work involves litigation, but we are also asked to provide consulting assistance in some cases. We work on both the plaintiff/government side and for law firms acting for those accused of anti-competitive conduct.&lt;/p&gt;
