&lt;p&gt;The Brattle Group, a privately held, global economics consulting firm, is looking for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Administrator &lt;/strong&gt;to join our&lt;strong&gt; Washington, DC &lt;/strong&gt;office. This full-time position is primarily responsible for project coordination and administrative support of Principals in a fast-paced, client-focused environment.&amp;nbsp; As a Senior Administrator, you are accountable for assisting the Principals you are assigned in their respective management group by facilitating their various day-to-day administrative responsibilities as well as providing a wide range of support to their projects, their teams, and practice area. This position takes day-to-day direction from the Principals and reports to the Director of Administration &amp;amp; Facilities. The Senior Administrator is a member of the Business Support Services (BSS) team, and provides general administrative support, as well as back-up support as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the day-to-day responsibilities of this role include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
